<h2>Books on Johnson</h2>

A complete bibliography? &#0151; Get serious.  These are just 
announcements of books about Johnson available on-line.

<ul>

<LI>J. C. D. Clark, <a
href="http://www.cup.org/Titles/47/0521473047.html">Samuel
Johnson</a> (Cambridge Univ. Press)

<li>Alvin Kernan, <a
href="http://pup.princeton.edu/titles/2448.html">Samuel Johnson
and the Impact of Print</a> (Princeton Univ. Press)

<li>Bruce Redford, <a
href="http://pup.princeton.edu/titles/5321.html">The Letters of
Samuel Johnson</a> (Princeton)

</ul>


<h2>The Club</h2>

<ul>

<li>"<a 
href="http://www.stockton.edu/~kinsellt/litresources/ayr/title2.html">Sons 
